comment:
* A class to hold a all necessary Visibility information corresponding to the same schema. This * pattern allows for easier association of these documents. * *

This does not correspond to any schema, the properties held in this class are kept in two * separate schemas, VisibilityConfig and PublicAclOverlay.

methods.name: public List<PackageIdentifier> getAllowedPackages()
methods.comment: Returns a list of {@link PackageIdentifier}s of packages that can access this schema.

methods.name: public Set<Set<Integer>> getRequiredPermissions()
methods.comment:
* Returns an array of Integers representing Android Permissions as defined in {@link
     * SetSchemaRequest.AppSearchSupportedPermission} that the caller must hold to access the schema
     * this {@link SchemaVisibilityConfig} represents.

methods.name: public PackageIdentifier getPubliclyVisibleTargetPackage()
methods.comment:
* Returns the {@link PackageIdentifier} of the package that will be used as the target package
     * in a call to {@link android.content.pm.PackageManager#canPackageQuery} to determine which
     * packages can access this publicly visible schema. Returns null if the schema is not publicly
     * visible.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
